    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a generous spray of <strong>cooking oil spray</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 5-6 min</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-crusted-double-basa-with-lentil-stew/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the onion is cooking, boil a kettle</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [260ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [340ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-crusted-double-basa-with-lentil-stew/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and finely chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-crusted-double-basa-with-lentil-stew/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>carrot, bay leaf[ves]</strong>,<strong> drained green lentils </strong>and<strong> stock</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until the carrots are tender, stirring occasionally \u2013 this is your <strong>lentil stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-crusted-double-basa-with-lentil-stew/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, zest <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s]</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining non-zested lemon</strong> into wedges</p><p>Chop your<strong> parsley </strong>finely, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-crusted-double-basa-with-lentil-stew/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine in a bowl your <strong>panko breadcrumbs, chopped parsley, lemon zest</strong> and <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>lemon breadcrumb mixture</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-crusted-double-basa-with-lentil-stew/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Lightly spray a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>cooking oil spray</strong> and add your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> then top with the <strong>lemon breadcrumb mixture</strong></p><p>Once the stew has 10 min left, put the tray[s] in the oven for 13-15 min or until the breadcrumbs are golden and the fish is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-crusted-double-basa-with-lentil-stew/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the carrots are tender, squeeze in the juice of the <strong>zested lemon[s]</strong>, add a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and season with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Discard the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> lemon-crusted fish </strong>over the <strong>lentil stew</strong> and garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge </strong>and the <strong>reserved parsley leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
